    <summary>Simple yet versatile library for generating graphs in the DOT language.</summary>
    
    <description>A simple solution for generating graphs in the DOT language. The output is a textual script that can be visualized and/or converted to an image with external tools. A handy one is a plugin for Visual Studio Code, named Graphviz Preview. There are also online tools like www.webgraphviz.com, where you can paste the script to view your graph.</description>
    
    <releaseNotes>- Added support for all available edge arrowheads with the filled, empty, and half-clipped variants. See https://github.com/mariusz-schimke/GiGraph/blob/1.5.0/README.md#arrowhead-shapes.

- Added support for edges with multiple arrowheads. See https://github.com/mariusz-schimke/GiGraph/blob/1.5.0/README.md#arrowhead-shapes.

- Added support for label justification (individual lines may be centered, left- or right-justified). See https://github.com/mariusz-schimke/GiGraph/blob/1.5.0/README.md#label-justification.

- Added support for label placeholders (element-specific escape sequences replaced with corresponding identifiers on graph visualization). See https://github.com/mariusz-schimke/GiGraph/blob/1.5.0/README.md#label-placeholders.

- Added support for attributes: headlabel, taillabel, image, imagepos, imagepath, group, ranksep, headclip, tailclip, colorscheme, rotate, pad, margin, size, ratio, labelfloat, labeldistance, labelangle, labelfontcolor, labelfontname, labelfontsize, minlen, len, weight, clusterrank, ordering, samehead, sametail, pack, sortv (attribute specifications available at http://www.graphviz.org/doc/info/attrs.html).

- Added separate classes to represent color combinations: DotDualColor, DotGradientColor, DotMultiColor.

- Added support for multiple graph/subgraph/cluster sections to support of the DOT grammar fully. See https://github.com/mariusz-schimke/GiGraph/blob/1.5.0/README.md#subsections.

- It is possible now to nullify attribute values (for some attributes it restores their original default value). See https://github.com/mariusz-schimke/GiGraph/blob/1.5.0/README.md#default-attributes.

- Refactoring.


See also https://github.com/mariusz-schimke/GiGraph/releases</releaseNotes>
